1
00:00:24,291 --> 00:00:25,458
[TAKUYA]
That woman.

2
00:00:25,541 --> 00:00:26,625
[inaudible]

3
00:00:26,708 --> 00:00:28,083
She's from Lacuna.

4
00:00:29,208 --> 00:00:31,125
[YUKI]
Are they heading to Lost, too?

5
00:00:36,208 --> 00:00:37,250
[TAKUYA]
Let's hurry.

6
00:00:37,333 --> 00:00:38,250
[YUKI]
Yeah.

7
00:00:38,333 --> 00:00:39,458
[motor scooter engine revving]

8
00:02:17,875 --> 00:02:19,458
[YUMIKO]
That's the antenna, huh?

9
00:02:19,541 --> 00:02:21,291
[KOUTA]
This is crazy.

10
00:02:23,416 --> 00:02:24,833
[EIJI]
In order for Takuya and Yuki

11
00:02:24,916 --> 00:02:26,750
to maintain their sanity
within Lost,

12
00:02:26,833 --> 00:02:29,000
we'll have to
continually call out to them,

13
00:02:29,083 --> 00:02:30,750
without a single pause.

14
00:02:30,833 --> 00:02:32,916
Okay, but, how?

15
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:36,250
Lacuna is equipped to do it.
We'll take advantage of that.

16
00:02:36,333 --> 00:02:37,791
[gasps]

17
00:02:37,875 --> 00:02:39,458
[EIJI] We're going to have
to hack into their system

18
00:02:39,541 --> 00:02:40,958
and use their antenna remotely.

19
00:02:41,041 --> 00:02:43,458
[KIKYO] But in order to do that,
we'll have to get in

20
00:02:43,541 --> 00:02:45,166
and take over their server room.

21
00:02:46,458 --> 00:02:49,458
♪

22
00:02:49,541 --> 00:02:50,916
We have intruders.

23
00:02:53,416 --> 00:02:54,791
[BOTH gasp]

24
00:02:56,250 --> 00:02:57,125
[grunts]

25
00:03:01,708 --> 00:03:03,500
-Go ahead.
-[YUJI] Hurry!

26
00:03:06,541 --> 00:03:09,541
♪

27
00:03:09,625 --> 00:03:11,458
-[rattles]
-[KOUTA grunts]

28
00:03:16,541 --> 00:03:18,083
[YUMIKO grunts]

29
00:03:25,083 --> 00:03:26,250
[computer beeps]

30
00:03:26,333 --> 00:03:28,041
[KOUTA on computer]
Okay on this side.

31
00:03:28,125 --> 00:03:30,083
[YUMIKO on computer]
Geek, we're all set.

32
00:03:30,166 --> 00:03:31,958
Roger that.

33
00:03:32,041 --> 00:03:35,500
This is cool. I haven't gotten
to go all out in a while.

34
00:03:39,458 --> 00:03:40,416
[gasps]

35
00:03:45,708 --> 00:03:46,833
[TAKUYA]
Shit.

36
00:03:48,416 --> 00:03:50,125
Are they predicting
our movements?

37
00:03:50,208 --> 00:03:51,708
That's what it seems like.

38
00:03:53,875 --> 00:03:55,166
[TAKUYA grunts]

39
00:03:59,416 --> 00:04:00,750
[BOTH gasp]

40
00:04:04,500 --> 00:04:05,875
[TAKUYA]
You.

41
00:04:22,250 --> 00:04:23,416
Takuya.

42
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:24,750
Yoshiaki.

43
00:04:25,916 --> 00:04:27,541
You guys havin' a party?

44
00:04:27,625 --> 00:04:29,458
Hey, how's everyone doing?

45
00:04:29,541 --> 00:04:31,083
[scoffs]

46
00:04:32,375 --> 00:04:34,208
What are you doing here?

47
00:04:36,041 --> 00:04:37,083
[YOSHIAKI]
Take these.

48
00:04:40,625 --> 00:04:42,333
You should be able
to stay connected to us

49
00:04:42,416 --> 00:04:43,750
from Lost using those.

50
00:04:45,250 --> 00:04:48,500
Geek and the gang are working
on it, making preparations.

51
00:04:48,583 --> 00:04:49,875
[YUKI]
Huh?

52
00:04:49,958 --> 00:04:52,458
[tires screeching in distance]

53
00:04:52,541 --> 00:04:53,916
[JACK]
Here they come.

54
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:56,583
Hey, just leave
the rest to us, okay?

55
00:04:57,583 --> 00:05:02,333
♪

56
00:05:02,416 --> 00:05:05,041
[ALL yelling]

57
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:10,208
[TAKUYA]
Here we go.

58
00:05:15,208 --> 00:05:17,750
Lost is just up ahead.
We'll be there soon.

59
00:05:17,833 --> 00:05:19,041
Prepare yourself.

60
00:05:20,375 --> 00:05:22,666
-[TAIYO] Suzuna.
-What is it?

61
00:05:22,750 --> 00:05:24,375
[TAIYO]
Thank you for your work.

62
00:05:24,458 --> 00:05:26,041
[SUZUNA]
Huh?

63
00:05:26,125 --> 00:05:28,708
[TAIYO] I'm very appreciative
for all you've done.

64
00:05:30,083 --> 00:05:31,583
[SUZUNA]
I don't deserve any praise.

65
00:05:31,666 --> 00:05:33,250
I was just doing my job.

66
00:05:38,041 --> 00:05:39,500
[KEIGO and YUJI panting]

67
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:53,833
There's no end.

68
00:06:08,583 --> 00:06:10,000
[BOTH gasp]

69
00:06:11,166 --> 00:06:13,875
Looks like It's been a few hours
since he was shot.

70
00:06:13,958 --> 00:06:16,166
Man, what the hell
is happening around here?

71
00:06:19,250 --> 00:06:21,125
[beeps]

72
00:06:21,208 --> 00:06:22,375
[MEN gasp]

73
00:06:22,458 --> 00:06:24,125
[BOTH groan]

74
00:06:26,958 --> 00:06:29,083
[MAN over radio]
Come in. What's happened?

75
00:06:29,166 --> 00:06:30,291
Please respond.

76
00:06:32,291 --> 00:06:33,708
We're dead if we don't hurry.

77
00:06:33,791 --> 00:06:35,791
You took the words
right outta my mouth.

78
00:06:35,875 --> 00:06:38,083
What's taking Geek so long?

79
00:06:38,166 --> 00:06:39,875
Keigo, are you there?

80
00:06:39,958 --> 00:06:42,916
Shut down the power
to the whole facility.

81
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:44,833
But then won't
the server room go down, too?

82
00:06:44,916 --> 00:06:46,333
Look, just do it!

83
00:06:46,416 --> 00:06:49,541
It seems Taiyo
is heading towards Lost.

84
00:06:49,625 --> 00:06:51,416
Whatever he's doing,
we can't let him get in

85
00:06:51,500 --> 00:06:52,958
Takuya and Yuki's way.

86
00:06:53,041 --> 00:06:55,333
Hey, Geek,
how's the decryption coming?

87
00:06:55,416 --> 00:06:57,708
I'm working on it.

88
00:06:57,791 --> 00:06:58,916
It's just...

89
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:02,208
This load is going to
drive me insane!

90
00:07:07,291 --> 00:07:09,458
You really plan to go
in there on your own?

91
00:07:11,291 --> 00:07:14,208
[TAIYO] You'll end up getting
involved if you stay here.

92
00:07:14,291 --> 00:07:16,708
Whether you stay
or immediately retreat

93
00:07:16,791 --> 00:07:18,375
is completely up to you.

94
00:07:28,333 --> 00:07:31,291
♪

95
00:07:56,958 --> 00:08:00,125
[SUZUNA] This is revenge for
all of the countless innocents.

96
00:08:01,875 --> 00:08:03,666
Those whose lives you stole.

97
00:08:09,166 --> 00:08:11,958
[MEN grunt]

98
00:08:12,041 --> 00:08:13,083
[MAN]
Huh?

99
00:08:13,166 --> 00:08:14,750
[beeping]

100
00:08:16,541 --> 00:08:18,041
There's a backup?

101
00:08:18,125 --> 00:08:20,458
This company is
capable of anything,

102
00:08:20,541 --> 00:08:23,208
but only as long as
the servers are working.

103
00:08:23,291 --> 00:08:24,625
[pounding on door]

104
00:08:24,708 --> 00:08:26,541
Now the doors won't open.

105
00:08:26,625 --> 00:08:29,083
It seems we've got
ourselves an actual siege.

106
00:08:39,666 --> 00:08:41,125
[BOTH gasp]

107
00:08:42,541 --> 00:08:45,333
♪

108
00:08:48,583 --> 00:08:51,333
[gasping weakly]

109
00:08:57,541 --> 00:08:58,666
[gasps]

110
00:08:58,750 --> 00:09:00,291
[SUZUNA groaning]

111
00:09:00,375 --> 00:09:03,791
[SUZUNA weakly]
Taiyo... has entered Lost.

112
00:09:06,916 --> 00:09:07,916
Hang in there, okay?

113
00:09:09,708 --> 00:09:12,416
[labored breathing]

114
00:09:13,583 --> 00:09:14,625
[SUZUNA]
Yuki...

115
00:09:15,958 --> 00:09:17,416
I know I...

116
00:09:17,500 --> 00:09:21,291
I've put you through
an unforgivable amount of pain.

117
00:09:23,708 --> 00:09:25,291
[gasps]

118
00:09:25,375 --> 00:09:26,666
Suzuna.

119
00:09:28,125 --> 00:09:30,166
It's okay.

120
00:09:30,250 --> 00:09:31,541
I deserve it.

121
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:36,541
Go. Please... hurry.

122
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:46,041
[TAKUYA] You even shot your
own subordinate, you bastard.

123
00:09:48,083 --> 00:09:48,916
[GEEK gasps]

124
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,708
Shit, come on!

125
00:09:50,791 --> 00:09:52,666
-[steady beep on computer]
-[KANA on computer] Yoo-hoo!

126
00:09:52,750 --> 00:09:55,166
-[GEEK gasps] Kana?
-[laughs]

127
00:09:56,291 --> 00:09:57,833
[KANA]
Guess where I am right now?

128
00:09:57,916 --> 00:09:59,000
The academy borough.

129
00:09:59,083 --> 00:10:01,250
[GEEK]
Huh? Who cares?

130
00:10:01,333 --> 00:10:03,000
[KANA] The tech here
is really state of the art.

131
00:10:03,083 --> 00:10:05,208
[GEEK] So what?
Are you kidding me right now?

132
00:10:05,291 --> 00:10:06,458
I'm a little busy!

133
00:10:06,541 --> 00:10:07,666
[KANA]
Well, I just connected you

134
00:10:07,750 --> 00:10:09,541
to the university's
supercomputer.

135
00:10:09,625 --> 00:10:11,875
You did what?

136
00:10:11,958 --> 00:10:14,083
Oh! You're a freakin' genius!

137
00:10:14,166 --> 00:10:16,291
Oh, stop. You got the skills,

138
00:10:16,375 --> 00:10:18,333
you're just bad
at following through.

139
00:10:18,416 --> 00:10:21,083
You gotta be a little craftier.

140
00:10:21,166 --> 00:10:24,083
All right, let's, do this!

141
00:10:24,166 --> 00:10:26,166
-Hmm!
-[ALL gasp]

142
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:30,208
[GEEK] The parallel processing
ramped up the decryption speed!

143
00:10:30,291 --> 00:10:32,833
Thanks so much!
This is gonna do it.

144
00:10:32,916 --> 00:10:34,791
♪

145
00:10:35,958 --> 00:10:37,416
[GEEK over radio]
Takuya. Yuki.

146
00:10:37,500 --> 00:10:38,958
Yeah, we're here.

147
00:10:39,041 --> 00:10:40,458
[GEEK]
Sorry for the wait.

148
00:10:40,541 --> 00:10:42,583
[TAKUYA]
We're about to head into Lost.

149
00:10:42,666 --> 00:10:44,125
Countin' on you, buddy.

150
00:10:44,208 --> 00:10:45,416
Got it.

151
00:10:45,500 --> 00:10:47,833
And, hey, both of you...

152
00:10:52,041 --> 00:10:53,875
get back alive.

153
00:10:53,958 --> 00:10:55,375
We'll be waiting for you.

154
00:10:58,708 --> 00:11:00,458
[YOSHIAKI]
Those two will find a way.

155
00:11:00,541 --> 00:11:01,583
They will.

156
00:11:01,666 --> 00:11:03,583
♪

157
00:11:04,666 --> 00:11:09,375
[ALL]
Go!

158
00:11:18,958 --> 00:11:20,916
[YUKI groaning]

159
00:11:23,375 --> 00:11:25,500
[monitor beeping]

160
00:11:25,583 --> 00:11:27,750
[rattling]

161
00:11:27,833 --> 00:11:29,208
[beeping rapidly]

162
00:11:32,916 --> 00:11:34,375
[machine powers on]

163
00:11:39,166 --> 00:11:41,583
♪

164
00:11:44,166 --> 00:11:45,833
[YUA]
No, I won't do it!

165
00:11:50,250 --> 00:11:52,375
I'm not going, you understand?

166
00:11:53,750 --> 00:11:55,208
I do, yeah.

167
00:11:56,666 --> 00:11:59,541
I know I have no right
to act so high and mighty.

168
00:12:04,125 --> 00:12:06,958
[RYOKO] You know, my father
was also caught in the Lost.

169
00:12:08,333 --> 00:12:11,375
Day after day,
it was all work, work, work.

170
00:12:11,458 --> 00:12:13,291
'Course, I knew being
a police officer meant

171
00:12:13,375 --> 00:12:15,416
he'd be busy all the time.

172
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:17,916
But I missed him,
and I was lonely.

173
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:20,833
It's been three years
since the Lost,

174
00:12:20,916 --> 00:12:23,041
and I know there are a lot
of people who've given up.

175
00:12:24,958 --> 00:12:26,333
But not me.

176
00:12:26,416 --> 00:12:28,500
I will never give up.

177
00:12:28,583 --> 00:12:31,666
I believe that my father
is still alive somewhere.

178
00:12:34,041 --> 00:12:35,916
[YUKI]
Everyone disappeared.

179
00:12:37,333 --> 00:12:39,041
That's just reality.

180
00:12:40,416 --> 00:12:42,916
And I'm so tired now.

181
00:12:44,375 --> 00:12:45,750
He really survived?

182
00:12:45,833 --> 00:12:48,416
[YUMIKO] If you continue
to head towards Lost,

183
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:50,500
he's going to keep on
appearing like that.

184
00:12:50,583 --> 00:12:52,000
Do you understand?

185
00:12:52,083 --> 00:12:54,041
It means you'll have to fight
your little brother.

186
00:12:54,125 --> 00:12:55,625
[YUKI gasps]

187
00:12:55,708 --> 00:12:57,833
Are you prepared
to do that again?

188
00:12:57,916 --> 00:12:59,041
Because if you're not,

189
00:12:59,125 --> 00:13:01,958
then please leave Takuya
out of this.

190
00:13:02,041 --> 00:13:03,541
[YUKI]
That wasn't him.

191
00:13:03,625 --> 00:13:05,458
That wasn't my brother.

192
00:13:06,750 --> 00:13:09,000
I'm sick of this.

193
00:13:09,083 --> 00:13:11,375
I don't care what happens.

194
00:13:11,458 --> 00:13:16,291
I don't care about my father,
or my brother, or even Takuya.

195
00:13:16,375 --> 00:13:18,416
I can't care!

196
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:19,666
[KOUTA groans]

197
00:13:19,750 --> 00:13:21,916
[distorted]
All I want is to rest!

198
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:23,833
-Oh, no.
-You okay?

199
00:13:23,916 --> 00:13:26,208
Yuki, hey, listen to me.

200
00:13:28,208 --> 00:13:30,083
You can do this.

201
00:13:30,166 --> 00:13:32,458
You're one of
the strongest people I know.

202
00:13:36,666 --> 00:13:38,791
[TAKUYA]
Hold on, you hear me?

203
00:13:40,916 --> 00:13:43,291
[static]

204
00:13:43,375 --> 00:13:45,750
My head feels like
it's gonna split.

205
00:13:47,291 --> 00:13:48,291
Damn it.

206
00:13:50,750 --> 00:13:51,916
[groans softly]

207
00:13:59,375 --> 00:14:00,375
Kouta.

208
00:14:05,916 --> 00:14:07,833
-[coughing]
-[footsteps approaching]

209
00:14:09,916 --> 00:14:12,083
[YUKI gasps in fear]

210
00:14:12,166 --> 00:14:13,250
[gasps]

211
00:14:19,041 --> 00:14:20,000
[groans sharply]

212
00:14:23,166 --> 00:14:24,625
[grunting]

213
00:14:24,708 --> 00:14:25,625
Stop it.

214
00:14:30,375 --> 00:14:33,708
[HORNET]
I can't. This is my job.

215
00:14:33,791 --> 00:14:34,875
[grunts]

216
00:14:34,958 --> 00:14:37,958
[groaning]

217
00:14:38,041 --> 00:14:40,375
I heard somewhere
you're a courier.

218
00:14:40,458 --> 00:14:44,291
So, I kill, and you deliver.

219
00:14:44,375 --> 00:14:46,041
It's all the same.

220
00:14:46,125 --> 00:14:48,208
How am I different?

221
00:14:48,291 --> 00:14:50,208
We're just cogs in a machine.

222
00:14:50,291 --> 00:14:52,666
Hapless puppets of fate.

223
00:14:52,750 --> 00:14:56,541
You and me, in the end,
we can do nothing

224
00:14:56,625 --> 00:14:58,166
even if we wanted to.

225
00:15:00,791 --> 00:15:01,583
[groans]

226
00:15:01,666 --> 00:15:03,375
[gasps]

227
00:15:03,458 --> 00:15:04,916
[YUMIKO]
Listen to me.

228
00:15:06,250 --> 00:15:07,875
Please don't go back to Lost.

229
00:15:07,958 --> 00:15:09,416
Stay away from there.

230
00:15:09,500 --> 00:15:11,958
I couldn't take it.

231
00:15:12,041 --> 00:15:14,458
I don't want to see you
get hurt again.

232
00:15:14,541 --> 00:15:17,166
You might not even come out
of there alive next time.

233
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:21,125
[TAKUYA] I don't wanna live
with regrets again.

234
00:15:21,208 --> 00:15:24,166
Not like last time. Not again.

235
00:15:27,291 --> 00:15:29,208
What do you mean,
"the investigation's closed"?

236
00:15:29,291 --> 00:15:30,916
Just exactly what I said.

237
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:33,625
It's no longer necessary
to have you at the academy.

238
00:15:33,708 --> 00:15:34,833
Why not?

239
00:15:34,916 --> 00:15:36,666
[KAIBARA]
It's already been decided.

240
00:15:36,750 --> 00:15:38,208
I can't accept this.

241
00:15:38,291 --> 00:15:40,083
Not when I'm so close
to the truth.

242
00:15:42,750 --> 00:15:44,666
[KAIBARA]
Remember something, Takuya.

243
00:15:44,750 --> 00:15:47,208
We aren't the police, okay?

244
00:15:47,291 --> 00:15:48,916
We're no heroes of justice.

245
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:50,625
[door closes]

246
00:15:50,708 --> 00:15:52,000
Mr. Kaibara, wait!

247
00:15:55,291 --> 00:15:56,625
[HINAKO]
Look at what we got.

248
00:15:56,708 --> 00:15:59,375
Someone gave
the school circus tickets.

249
00:15:59,458 --> 00:16:01,583
Would you like
to come with us?

250
00:16:01,666 --> 00:16:03,916
♪

251
00:16:12,916 --> 00:16:16,541
[TAKUYA] This is the past,
and I can't change the past.

252
00:16:18,916 --> 00:16:21,583
Does that mean I'm supposed to
just let people die again?

253
00:16:21,666 --> 00:16:23,250
[sighs]

254
00:16:23,333 --> 00:16:25,083
If that's true...

255
00:16:25,166 --> 00:16:28,166
then I think it's better
if I go, too.

256
00:16:28,250 --> 00:16:29,625
No regrets.

257
00:16:29,708 --> 00:16:30,791
Not this time.

258
00:16:30,875 --> 00:16:33,791
Yeah, I'll go.

259
00:16:34,875 --> 00:16:36,583
No, you can't, Takuya.

260
00:16:36,666 --> 00:16:37,875
Takuya!

261
00:16:37,958 --> 00:16:39,500
-[electrical humming]
-The white noise.

262
00:16:40,958 --> 00:16:43,750
It's very possible they aren't
able to hear us anymore.

263
00:16:44,833 --> 00:16:47,416
[GEEK]
Takuya! Don't do this.

264
00:16:47,500 --> 00:16:49,625
You hear me?

265
00:16:52,458 --> 00:16:55,375
Takuya!

266
00:16:55,458 --> 00:16:57,166
Yuki!

267
00:16:57,250 --> 00:16:59,916
♪

268
00:17:35,208 --> 00:17:37,375
I know you're here, Daichi.

269
00:17:45,916 --> 00:17:49,333
Believe me, as much as I'd like
to reminisce about the past,

270
00:17:49,416 --> 00:17:51,833
I'm afraid I don't have
the time today.

271
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:55,750
First, I have to
erase you completely.

272
00:17:55,833 --> 00:17:58,791
Then, I must finish the portal.

273
00:17:58,875 --> 00:18:01,791
[GEEK]
Answer me, buddy. Come on.

274
00:18:01,875 --> 00:18:06,166
[EIJI] Listen, all we can do
is trust in their bond now.

275
00:18:06,250 --> 00:18:08,041
[KIKYO] As long as they keep
supporting each other,

276
00:18:08,125 --> 00:18:10,333
their memories will stay intact.

277
00:18:10,416 --> 00:18:12,500
If one of them falters, then...

278
00:18:17,958 --> 00:18:19,541
[YUKI]
Oh, Takuya.

279
00:18:19,625 --> 00:18:21,041
Are you okay?

280
00:18:21,125 --> 00:18:23,041
[groans weakly]

281
00:18:23,125 --> 00:18:24,500
[GEEK]
Takuya!

282
00:18:24,583 --> 00:18:27,000
Oh, hey, Geek.

283
00:18:27,083 --> 00:18:28,791
Well, let's go.

284
00:18:28,875 --> 00:18:30,333
[GEEK]
Don't give me that.

285
00:18:30,416 --> 00:18:32,416
Hold on. Are you okay?

286
00:18:32,500 --> 00:18:33,708
[TAKUYA]
No prob.

287
00:18:33,791 --> 00:18:35,791
[GEEK]
You're nuts. Of course there is.

288
00:18:37,333 --> 00:18:39,291
[TAKUYA]
Who was that girl?

289
00:18:39,375 --> 00:18:41,291
[GEEK]
How would I know?

290
00:18:41,375 --> 00:18:42,666
[YUKI gasps softly]

291
00:18:42,750 --> 00:18:45,250
♪

292
00:18:45,333 --> 00:18:47,916
[motor scooter approaching]

293
00:19:00,625 --> 00:19:02,958
[TAKUYA]
So tired.

294
00:19:03,041 --> 00:19:05,375
My whole body hurts.

295
00:19:05,458 --> 00:19:08,416
What... What was I doing again?

296
00:19:10,333 --> 00:19:13,500
Well, who cares?

297
00:19:13,583 --> 00:19:15,416
What does it matter?

298
00:19:15,500 --> 00:19:17,958
It's not like
I can do anything, anyway.

299
00:19:21,083 --> 00:19:25,916
[YUKI] Hey, what's your idea
of a normal life, Takuya?

300
00:19:27,208 --> 00:19:30,083
[TAKUYA] Having a place to stay,
a place to work,

301
00:19:30,166 --> 00:19:32,625
and some friends to be with.

302
00:19:32,708 --> 00:19:34,041
[YUKI]
That sounds nice.

303
00:19:35,416 --> 00:19:37,041
[TAKUYA] Normal is
the best kind of happiness.

304
00:19:38,208 --> 00:19:40,375
I agree. It sounds great.

305
00:19:41,708 --> 00:19:42,875
Once everything is over,

306
00:19:42,958 --> 00:19:45,333
I hope I'll be able
to have that.

307
00:19:45,416 --> 00:19:46,833
[TAKUYA]
Who is this girl?

308
00:19:46,916 --> 00:19:50,208
[YUKI] I wonder
what's the best place to live.

309
00:19:50,291 --> 00:19:52,666
I'd like a place
with a cool view.

310
00:19:52,750 --> 00:19:54,708
[YUKI]
A house beside the sea.

311
00:19:54,791 --> 00:19:56,708
I think I'd like a cat, too.

312
00:19:59,125 --> 00:20:00,791
[TAKUYA]
A big window would be good.

313
00:20:00,875 --> 00:20:02,375
The cat would love it.

314
00:20:02,458 --> 00:20:05,583
[YUKI] Wonder what color
the curtains should be.

315
00:20:05,666 --> 00:20:07,666
-[TAKUYA] Blue's nice.
-[YUKI] What?

316
00:20:07,750 --> 00:20:12,291
Come on, a blue sea
behind blue curtains? Huh?

317
00:20:12,375 --> 00:20:13,375
Who are you?

318
00:20:15,791 --> 00:20:16,958
[TAKUYA]
Ah, good point.

319
00:20:17,041 --> 00:20:18,166
Green, then.

320
00:20:20,041 --> 00:20:23,125
[YUKI]
Yeah. I like the sound of that.

321
00:20:23,208 --> 00:20:25,250
And I guess
the furniture should match.

322
00:20:26,958 --> 00:20:29,333
[TAKUYA] I'll come visit
from time to time.

323
00:20:29,416 --> 00:20:30,916
[YUKI]
Yes, and I'll make dinner.

324
00:20:32,083 --> 00:20:34,375
[TAKUYA] Now that I think of it,
I am pretty hungry.

325
00:20:34,458 --> 00:20:36,416
[YUKI] No way,
what're you talking about?

326
00:20:36,500 --> 00:20:38,500
It has to be white rice
and miso soup.

327
00:20:38,583 --> 00:20:40,250
[TAKUYA]
Ah, a traditionalist.

328
00:20:40,333 --> 00:20:41,583
Hey.

329
00:20:41,666 --> 00:20:44,833
It must be wonderful
living a normal life.

330
00:20:44,916 --> 00:20:45,958
[TAKUYA]
Yeah.

331
00:20:47,125 --> 00:20:49,041
[YUKI]
I'm determined not to forget.

332
00:20:49,125 --> 00:20:50,208
[TAKUYA]
Same.

333
00:20:50,291 --> 00:20:52,083
No matter what happens
after this,

334
00:20:52,166 --> 00:20:54,916
let's try to remember,
that's where we're headed.

335
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:57,791
♪

336
00:21:16,541 --> 00:21:19,083
[motor scooter engine revving]

337
00:21:24,166 --> 00:21:27,208
Takuya, you saved us.

338
00:21:27,291 --> 00:21:29,083
Thank you.

339
00:21:29,166 --> 00:21:31,541
No, it's thanks to you.

340
00:21:31,625 --> 00:21:33,708
♪

341
00:21:35,375 --> 00:21:37,500
You haven't changed
at all, have you?

342
00:21:37,583 --> 00:21:39,333
Even in this new form.

343
00:21:45,583 --> 00:21:47,458
[TAKUYA]
Taiyo.

344
00:21:47,541 --> 00:21:49,166
[YUKI]
Father?

345
00:21:49,250 --> 00:21:51,375
♪

346
00:21:52,750 --> 00:21:53,708
No!

347
00:21:53,791 --> 00:21:57,208
Stop it!

348
00:23:36,958 --> 00:23:39,166
♪

349
00:23:43,541 --> 00:23:45,791
[YUKI and TAKUYA]
Next episode, "Future."

